ReportText: PROCEDURE: CR CHEST 2V COMPARISON: None. INDICATIONS: Acute onset cough for one month. No fever. No surgeries. Initial episode of care. FINDINGS: LUNGS: Normal. No significant pulmonary parenchymal abnormalities. VASCULATURE: Normal. Unremarkable pulmonary vasculature. CARDIAC: Normal. No cardiac silhouette abnormality or cardiomegaly. MEDIASTINUM: Normal. No visible mass or adenopathy. PLEURA: Normal. No effusion or pleural thickening. BONES: Normal. No fracture or visible bony lesion. OTHER: Negative. CONCLUSION: Normal examination.
